HEADWORD: Thermometrical
<hw>Ther`mo*met"ric*al</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[Cf. F. <ets>thermom⟦eacute⟧trique</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Of or pertaining to a thermometer; <as>as, the
<ex>thermometrical</ex> scale or tube</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Made, or ascertained, by means of a thermometer;
<as>as, <ex>thermometrical</ex> observations</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Thermometrically</ent>⟦br⟧
